 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6989/resize-issue-with-urxvt/?answer=7039#post-id-7039</link><description>As pointed out by Airblader this is an urxvt issue. The workaround posted by Adaephon didn't really work that well for me. Therefore I had a look at the source code of urxvt and  posted a patch for this issue on the urxvt mailing list:

http://lists.schmorp.de/pipermail/rxvt-unicode/2015q4/002196.html

Besides the issue mentioned here, this also fixes some other resizing problems of urxvt.</description><pubDate>Sat, 24 Oct 2015 22:06:28 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6989/resize-issue-with-urxvt/?answer=7039#post-id-7039</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Airblader for &lt;p&gt;When the urxvt terminal is resized (for example by adding new windows), it cuts off the output of the terminal. Here is a video demonstrating this:&lt;/p&gt;

